        <hr noshade size="2" color="#545A7D">
        
         That said, here's a few things to think about.</P><P>The jist of this process is to fear the others to get them out of camp then single pull the last.  Feigning keeps the feared ones from agroing you.<BR>WARNING:  I have ZERO idea if this works. It's just something I kicked around when playing my SK.<BR>WARNING TWO: I've only been in ME once and got wiped out.<BR>WARNING THREE: I don't know BEANS about the Coterie<BR>1. select one.<BR>2. fear it.<BR>3. feign.<BR>4. get up.<BR>5. select another.<BR>6. fear it.<BR>7. feign.<BR>8. get up.<BR>9. pull the single.<BR>10. kill it</P><P></P><P>This MAY also work. The jist is to fear one into the agro range of your pet and then to feign to clear agro from the other two.  this will only work it the command "/pet attack" works  based on the agro radius of the pet and not your own.  If you try this and get the result "i don't see one of those around here" or "that is not a legal target" or whatever the pet says when the target is out of range then it won't work.<BR>WARNING:  I have ZERO idea if this works. It's just something I kicked around when playing my SK.  A SK pet is not near tough enough to even think about trying this, so this idea has even LESS thought put into it than the last one.<BR>- park pet down path from the camp.<BR>- go to the opposite side of the camp.<BR>- fear one.  It will run toward the pet. Others will come to kill you.<BR>- order pet to attack feared one after it has moved far enough from the camp. <BR>- feign.<BR>- get up and go help pet.</P><P>Finally Here's one that definiatly won't work.<BR>- summon a monk pet<BR>- select a vampire<BR>- /pet feign spilt %t<BR>- kill the vampire.</P><P></P><P> <a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
