		<a name="60857"></a>
		<img src="icon_posticon.gif" border="0" hspace="3"><font color="white" face="Verdana" size="2">Posted&nbsp;-&nbsp;08/19/2002&nbsp;:&nbsp; 13:32:29</font>

		&nbsp;<a href="pop_profile.asp?mode=display&amp;id=2677"><img src="icon_profile.gif" height="15" width="15" alt="Show Profile" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>
        
			&nbsp;<a href="JavaScript:openWindow('pop_mail.asp?id=2677')"><img src="icon_email.gif" height="15" width="15" alt="Email Poster" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>

        &nbsp;<a href="post.asp?method=ReplyQuote&amp;REPLY_ID=60857&amp;TOPIC_ID=7315&amp;FORUM_ID=2&amp;CAT_ID=1&amp;Forum_Title=General+Discussions&amp;Topic_Title=How+to+break+up+a+camp%3F%3F%3F+HELP&amp;M="><img src="icon_reply_topic.gif" height="15" width="15" alt="Reply with Quote" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>

        <hr noshade size="2" color="#545A7D">
        
         First off - know that this earring is rare.  From what I can tell it's no less rare than say the Idol offa cheif in Droga.  I'd imagine an average of 200+ vampires killed before you see this NICE earring.. although i haven't truely put that to the test (camped them a few times for about 8 hours straight, then other times for an hour or two.. didn't really count spawns, although I should have)  But do not fear- their other drop are not shabby at all.  Most common will be Coterie Junk armor/weapons.  Hardly great for even twinking the lowest of characters (considering the rock bottom prices you can find on better noobie gear in Bazaar :D), but the Coterie long and short swords look very cool on tanks .. alas are bugged with pets.  I always get a spear graphic.</P><P>Next on the loot list is Shrouded boots- Camp all your twinks here to loot a pair because you will see many.  No drop, and relatively solid in my opinion.  12 ac, 4 to all stats.  I mean 12 ac!  That's decent.. not uber, but you can't ask for much more if you're not even trying to farm for a twink.</P><P>They will drop lvl 51ish spells uncommonly as well- I managed to bag a few shaman spells (all luclin spells, as you'd imagine) and I *think* I got a copy of Epitah of life also (undead-only DoT for clerics- relatively sought after, at least it was a few months back).  Probably they can drop Degeneration also, although I didn't see it drop.</P><P>Next up is kind of random stuff- Earring of Magi'Kot (no-drop mage earring) and I forget what.  A VERY nice ranged idol for tanks (war, pal, shd) can drop also- I've seen it two times total.  As most of ME's drops it's also no-drop.. makes a Idol of the Thorned look like a peice of crap (Grodans idol: 12 ac, 12 str, 10 agi, 25 hp, 5 sv cold, 5 sv poison).  If you are lucky enough to loot this with your tank alt you won't be replacing it till you're hunting N. ToV, Ssra, etc etc.  </P><P>Beyond that you have your Ethereal Mist Earing.. and Even beyond that there's *supposedly* an earring called simply "Ethereal Earring".. 20 ac, 8 wis/int, 50 mana, 5 sv All.  Reports that I've seen say it did drop in the first 2 months after Luclin was released - MIA from then on out.  I think it's safe to say it was removed from their loot tables because of just being insanely nice loot for not being on a 65+ mob.</P><P>Pulling the camp?  I never really pulled them until lvl 60, and I am of the breed (yes, it's true) that did 99% of 59 in Katta (more on this later) .. so I've never had a problem single pulling them. I have had lvl 60 Tanks (mostly rangers who I hunt ME with) tell me they cannot single pull them w/o harmony.. which only means one thing.  Faction!  Indeed- they con ally to me.  As we learned in School the higher your faction the less an aggro range the mob will have in reaction to you (Well it's faction + your lvl + their agressiveness, right?).  Hunt in Katta like MAD and you will have all of the Coterie inviting you to all their parties.  After you've knocked your faction down with them to Amiable or the like (Would take forever in ME, although the named in TM drop your faction much quicker) head straight back to katta and whip some more guards around (If unfamiliar with Katta tactics start searching.. there's probably 20 posts outlining Katta tactics already)</P><P>Most likely you won't be able to single pull them I'd imagine until lvl 58-59 even with max ally faction.. but it sure gives you a hell of a lot better chance of them "forgetting" about you when you FD and they start back to spawn points (of course FD splitting deals more with assist-range than Aggro-range...luckily both are reduced with high faction).  I normally pull with snare, then immediately slow the bugger - Regardless of if I'll have tanks/pet to rumble with it.  They flurry (/boggle) and also proc a nice lifetap.. and can stun you.  You really want them slown (and more so want them charmed.. but alas I've read we can't Dire Charm these.. even the lower lvl ones  /cry).</P><P>As lvl ranges go- most of the ME ones are 49-51, but a few of them are 53 or 54 - and the 53-54 variations are quite a bit trickier, proving to be much more skilled at resisting my roots and slows.  But they die just the same as their lower lvl brethern  :)</P><P>Hope this helps, and sorry if it was Too much information.  I might very well be wrong about some of this, perhaps even flat-out dead-wrong.. it's been a few months since I hunted them (not very impressive exp at 60 and even if I had 7 twinks all of them would have the boots by now.  Earring SO rare, and Grodan's Idol pretty rare itself)  Mind you the main camp is 3 vampires total (one of which is a PH for a mob that drops a quest item for some gay cloak in.. you guessed it- Katta!) that spawn on 20 min timers I think.. if you felt up to it there's scores of bats and Skellies nearby, and if constantly killing would make for a decent exp camp.  Once I have dire charm I will be spending some time here with a DC'd bat and scores of slain undead :)</P><P>Kumiko D'Synn<BR>60 Defiler <BR>Fusion Of Flame<BR>Terris Thule Server<BR>(Defiler just sounds much more *evil* than "warlock". /rude Verant)<a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
