         "One thing to add, Thank you Ziko for your help on HHK thin this weekend. I finally got it down, and dinged 55 :) Now I had the same problem in Scarlet Desert last night, trying to one pull the dudes on the hill. I will try what some of the usefull people have posted here to split them."</P><P>Scarlet desert is a bit differnt to pull the coterie.   you can use alot of wall tricks and agro tricks to always pull just one.  I recomend using slow to pull as it has less agro radius.</P><P>basicaly just pull the 3 up front, first to right, then the one up ffront on left, then the one closest to inner castle. then walk up on the right side of the ledge near where you just pulled one from. turn to your left, pull the one by the wall.<BR>next head out back. pull the one under the fallen wall. then pull the one that spawns above him.  next pull the one to the left of the platform, and then the one to the right.</P><P>in SD it is all about your positioning when you pull as so to keep you pull out of agro range of any adds.  just take a look at the area, and play with the pathing thier a bit. you should be single pulling it in no time.  the only part you have to FD split is the 2 that spawn outside with the one that they agro inside.  other than that it is all easy.</P><P><center><b>Bringer of Darkness</b><BR><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=11832" target="_blank"><img src="http://members.cox.net/umbrae/pic.jpg" border=0></a><BR><a href="http://members.cox.net/umbrae/topless.jpg" target="_blank">Signature Pic R</a></center><a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
